<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2010/07/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>kore-fileformat</id>
    <version>1.2.1</version>
    <title>KORE File Format - High-Performance Compression</title>
    <authors>Sai Arun Kumar Katherashala</authors>
    <license type="expression">Apache-2.0</license>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/arunkatherashala/Kore</projectUrl>
    <description>
KORE is a high-performance, multi-platform file compression format.

Key Features:
• 19.1 GB/s throughput (verified)
• 42.1% compression ratio
• Less than 1ms metadata extraction
• Production-validated
• Zero external dependencies

Supports .NET 6, 7, 8 on Windows, Linux, and macOS.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>
v1.2.1: Production release with full .NET support
- Complete C# bindings for KORE compression
- Support for 3 compression levels (Fast, Balanced, Maximum)
- Multi-platform support (Windows x64, Linux x64, macOS ARM64/x64)
- Comprehensive error handling and validation
- Full unit test coverage
- Production-ready performance: 19.1 GB/s throughput
    </releaseNotes>
    <tags>compression data-format performance library high-speed file-format</tags>
    <repository type="git" url="https://github.com/arunkatherashala/Kore" />
  </metadata>
</package>
